# AI Hub - UI smoke test (screenshot every UI change)

Qt layouts look fine in code and still clip, overlap, or strike text
through at runtime. So **every time you add or change UI** you MUST
render it and look at the pixels before declaring the task done. Do not
rely on reading the code alone.

## When this is mandatory

Any change that builds Qt widgets: a new/edited `build_view` or
`build_context`, a new section under `src/sections/<key>/`, or a shared
widget under `src/components/**` / `src/qt/widgets.py`. Pure
backend/prompt/string edits with no widget change are exempt.

## How to run

```bash
# Default = the app minimum size (1220x760), where right-edge clipping
# shows up first. Screenshots land in the git-ignored .smoke/ folder.
python tools/smoke_shot.py --section ai_linkedin --lang cs --theme dark
python tools/smoke_shot.py --section my_profile  --lang en --theme light
python tools/smoke_shot.py --all          # every visible section
```

Then **open the PNG** in `.smoke/` and look. To inspect a suspect spot
at the pixel level, crop + magnify with Qt:

```python
from PySide6.QtGui import QImage
img = QImage(r".smoke\ai_linkedin-cs-dark-1220x760.png")
img.copy(img.width() - 230, 0, 230, img.height()).scaled(690, img.height() * 3).save(r".smoke\crop.png")
```

## What to check (fix, then re-shoot until clean)

- Nothing is clipped at the right edge or cut off at the bottom.
- No widget overlaps another (icon over text, status icon over a wrapped
  second line - see [qt-text.mdc](qt-text.mdc)).
- No text is struck through, elided unexpectedly, or truncated mid-word.
- Scrollbars sit in the gutter and do not crowd cards' rounded corners.
- Looks correct in **both** themes (`--theme dark`/`light`) and **both**
  languages (`--lang cs`/`en`); Czech is longer and clips first.

The harness prints `SMOKE_PASS` when it saved every screenshot, but that
only means the render succeeded - the visual check is still on you.

## Clean up when you're done (mandatory)

Smoke screenshots are **throwaway debugging artefacts**, not deliverables.
Once you have eyeballed them and the UI looks right, **delete them** - do
not leave PNGs lying around in `.smoke/` after the task. Wipe the folder
as the last step, after the visual check passes:

```bash
rmdir /s /q .smoke      REM Windows
rm -rf .smoke           # macOS / Linux
```

Re-running the harness recreates `.smoke/` automatically, so deleting it
is always safe. Also delete any throwaway crop / diagnostic scripts you
dropped in there while investigating.

## Don't

- Do not commit `.smoke/` (it is git-ignored).
- Do not leave the screenshots behind once the check is done - wipe
  `.smoke/` at the end of the task (see above).
- Do not move the harness under `src/` - it must stay in `tools/` so the
  PyInstaller hooks and section auto-discovery never pick it up.
